"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-03-paris-2024-olympics-ajayi-ashe-advance-into-100m-mens-semis\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Kanyinsola Ajayi and Favour Ashe claimed a place in the men's 100m semi-finals at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games on Saturday.  The duo are making their debut at the Olympic Games.  Ajayi won Heat 5 in 10.02s, beating Olympics champion Lamont Marcell Jacobs into second position at 10.05s.  Ghana's Abdul-Rasheed Saminu came third in a time of 10.06s.  Ashe finished fourth in Heat 4 behind Jamaica's Oblique Seville, Japan's Abdul Hakim Sani Brown and Thailand's Thurpool Bonboon.  Ashe, however, sealed his place in the semis after grabbing the last non-automatic spot.  In swimming, Adaku Nwandu finished second in Heat 6 of women's 50m Freestyle behind Elizaveta Pecherskikh.  The 16-year-old, however, failed to make it to the final.  Guardiola breaks silence on leaving Man City to take England job  Transfer: Go and shine - Saka reacts as midfielder leaves for Arsenal's rivals  Championship: Ajayi elated to be back after AFCON injury  Championship: Ajayi returns from injury in Hull City's defeat to Millwall  Championship: Ajayi poised for Hull City comeback after injury layoff  Championship: Ajayi nears Hull City return after injury layoff  Championship: Ajayi set for Hull City return after injury layoff  Hull City manager Jakirovic reveals when injured Super Eagles' Ajayi will play again  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"